                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14477372" author="paulk" created="Thu, 21 Jun 2007 06:57:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I applied a fix for this. For the record, old behaviour was:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;/ was only allowed if preceded by an odd number of \ characters. All characters were preserved.&lt;br/&gt;
\ at the end of a line escaped the end of line (i.e. acts as continuation character) so long as it wasn&apos;t preceded by an odd number of \ characters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;New behaviour is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;\ escapes end of line and / in which case the \ is removed. In all other cases, \ is preserved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477393" author="paulk" created="Thu, 21 Jun 2007 07:05:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Correct fix version&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
